{
  "texts": [
    "We recorded the species and taxonomic class of the study organism, and the ejaculate traits measured in the study (see Supplementary Notes 5 for definitions of each trait).",
    "The ejaculate traits were either measures of sperm/ejaculate quantity (e.g.",
    "sperm concentration, sperm number, and ejaculate volume), sperm performance (e.g.",
    "sperm motility, velocity, viability), or intra-cellular measures of sperm quality (e.g.",
    "oxidative stress in sperm, DNA damage to sperm, sperm telomere length)."
  ]
}